headlines.description: — Trae Young threw a long pass to hit A.J. Griffin for a wide-open layup at the overtime buzzer and the Atlanta Hawks, after rallying late in regulation, beat the undermanned Toronto Raptors 124-122 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young hits Griffin for OT buzzer-beater, Hawks top Raptors

headlines.description: — Aaron Nesmith made two free throws with 9.6 seconds left and the Indiana Pacers came up with a final defensive stop to beat the Orlando Magic 114-113 on Saturday night to open a two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers hold off Magic 114-113 to open 2-game set in Indy

headlines.description: — Against another short-handed team, the Timberwolves again came up big on the road.

events.name: Utah Jazz at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — -Jordan Clarkson scored 28 points, including eight straight in the final 1:48, in the Utah Jazz’s 118-113 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz beat Blazers 118-113 to take Western Conference lead

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at LA Clippers

headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers hit 21 3-pointers in 119-97 rout of Spurs
